      },
      "date": "2022-04-07 16:07:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\nSo I didn't see this earlier. I need to ask for the ktime change are those variables being handled all locally on the node. I mean their is no chance that the ktime values are being compared to values sent from other nodes. Lastly are those values used in any debug messages. For debug messages it is better to map the ktime value to real world clocks for logging purposes.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "e11d47018badfef3ec8142f8c01aa00d11f7f0e0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 148,
        "name": "Chris Horn",
        "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
        "username": "hornc"
      },
      "date": "2022-04-07 16:24:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 6:\n\n> So I didn't see this earlier. I need to ask for the ktime change\n > are those variables being handled all locally on the node. I mean\n > their is no chance that the ktime values are being compared to\n > values sent from other nodes.\n\nThe values are entirely local.\n\n > Lastly are those values used in any\n > debug messages. For debug messages it is better to map the ktime\n > value to real world clocks for logging purposes.\n\nlpni_last_alive is reported in a debug message and net_last_alive is output in a proc_lnet_nis()",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 6
